<td>Dual of rule 301.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>303</td>
<td><img class="tex" alt="\displaystyle e^{i a x}" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/math/1/a/0/1a03ae428735720252c40a614ed5557d.png" /></td>
<td><img class="tex" alt="\displaystyle \delta\left(\xi - \frac{a}{2\pi}\right)" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/math/3/2/8/328f831746f9f086e7eaef71d1fcc16d.png" /></td>
<td><img class="tex" alt="\displaystyle \sqrt{2 \pi}\cdot \delta(\omega - a)" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/math/4/4/8/4480e89b3e00b45f9fef5d2fab8d8c6e.png" /></td>
<td><img class="tex" alt="\displaystyle 2 \pi\delta(\nu - a)" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/math/7/7/b/77b692ccf1a4bd2eba42e0a3b78efe6d.png" /></td>
<td>This follows from 103 and 301.</td>
</tr>
