<td>304</td>
<td><img class="tex" alt="\displaystyle \cos (a x)" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/math/3/a/d/3ad7f07693be93ea5b4c93062ab0c887.png" /></td>
<td><img class="tex" alt="\displaystyle \frac{\displaystyle \delta\left(\xi - \frac{a}{2\pi}\right)+\delta\left(\xi+\frac{a}{2\pi}\right)}{2}" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/math/a/6/e/a6ea37c221a0beb1c9e71e86369f9b96.png" /></td>
<td><img class="tex" alt="\displaystyle \sqrt{2 \pi}\cdot\frac{\delta(\omega-a)+\delta(\omega+a)}{2}\," src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/math/2/f/b/2fbec44b64717c174f7520c2419be23d.png" /></td>
<td><img class="tex" alt="\displaystyle \pi\left(\delta(\nu-a)+\delta(\nu+a)\right)" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/math/6/f/5/6f5b06c670d3e001ab05c82f5843539a.png" /></td>
<td>This follows from rules 101 and 303 using <a href="/wiki/Eulers_formula_in_complex_analysis" title="Eulers formula in complex analysis" class="mw-redirect">Euler's formula</a>: <img class="tex" alt="\textstyle \cos(a x) = " src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/math/c/d/b/cdb9574afd52c959044c8a6e0910b180.png" /><br />
<p><img class="tex" alt="(e^{i a x} + e^{-i a x})/2." src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/math/e/a/0/ea09d6c29fcb01adb3ff9e4b9ab382d6.png" /></p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>305</td>
<td><img class="tex" alt="\displaystyle \sin( ax)" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/math/4/3/2/432eb26b772d1d71838aad16d18340d2.png" /></td>
<td><img class="tex" alt="\displaystyle \frac{\displaystyle\delta\left(\xi-\frac{a}{2\pi}\right)-\delta\left(\xi+\frac{a}{2\pi}\right)}{2i}" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/math/c/c/0/cc07778acddfb3e3a51d3d221512dcc8.png" /></td>
<td><img class="tex" alt="\displaystyle \sqrt{2 \pi}\cdot\frac{\delta(\omega-a)-\delta(\omega+a)}{2i}" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/math/f/a/3/fa38448fd8f88df4d4838566bb1d39a7.png" /></td>
<td><img class="tex" alt="\displaystyle -i\pi\left(\delta(\nu-a)-\delta(\nu+a)\right)" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/math/7/7/0/770a63f9211695f594e57bab2834d5df.png" /></td>
<td>This follows from 101 and 303 using <img class="tex" alt="\textstyle \sin(a x) = " src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/math/4/d/e/4def482c6fe0dc24123264aa65db354c.png" /><br />
<p><img class="tex" alt="(e^{i a x} - e^{-i a x})/(2i)." src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/math/d/c/7/dc7ee59d518f646a7a612cf1eccdb748.png" /></p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>306</td>
<td><img class="tex" alt="\displaystyle \cos ( a x^2 ) " src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/math/9/3/9/93939bb55a51a4cb9829fb46efe9008c.png" /></td>
